   668/// A simple flow layout that wraps children to the next line when they exceed width.
   669private struct FlowLayout: Layout {
   670    var spacing: CGFloat = 8
   671
   672    func sizeThatFits(proposal: ProposedViewSize, subviews: Subviews, cache: inout ()) -> CGSize {
   673        let result = arrange(proposal: proposal, subviews: subviews)
   674        return result.size
   675    }
   676
   677    func placeSubviews(in bounds: CGRect, proposal: ProposedViewSize, subviews: Subviews, cache: inout ()) {
   678        let result = arrange(proposal: ProposedViewSize(width: bounds.width, height: bounds.height), subviews: subviews)
   679        for (index, position) in result.positions.enumerated() {
   680            subviews[index].place(
   681                at: CGPoint(x: bounds.minX + position.x, y: bounds.minY + position.y),
   682                proposal: .unspecified
   683            )
   684        }
   685    }
   686
   687    private func arrange(proposal: ProposedViewSize, subviews: Subviews) -> (size: CGSize, positions: [CGPoint]) {
   688        let maxWidth = proposal.width ?? .infinity
   689        var positions: [CGPoint] = []
   690        var x: CGFloat = 0
   691        var y: CGFloat = 0
   692        var rowHeight: CGFloat = 0
   693        var totalWidth: CGFloat = 0
   694
   695        for subview in subviews {
   696            let size = subview.sizeThatFits(.unspecified)
   697            if x + size.width > maxWidth, x > 0 {
   698                x = 0
   699                y += rowHeight + spacing
   700                rowHeight = 0
   701            }
   702            positions.append(CGPoint(x: x, y: y))
   703            rowHeight = max(rowHeight, size.height)
   704            x += size.width + spacing
   705            totalWidth = max(totalWidth, x - spacing)
   706        }
   707
   708        return (CGSize(width: totalWidth, height: y + rowHeight), positions)
   709    }
   710}
